# motion graphics
Motion graphics are pieces of animation or digital footage which create the illusion of motion or
rotation, and are usually combined with audio for use in multimedia projects. Motion graphics are
usually displayed via electronic media technology, but may also be displayed via manual powered technology.

Animation (*techniques) >>> Motion Graphics 

    Explainer videos
    Walkthroughs/Instructional videos
    UI animation
    Dynamic logos
    Dynamic icons
    Animated page titles
    Animated infographics
    Presentations
    Broadcasting motion graphics
    GIFs

## text manipulation in blender is NOT that great
- resizing and aligning based on perspective and #words

## Techniques
lettering animation
3D objects (VC Element 3D)
particle simulations (Trapcode Particular / Newton) or
character animation (Duik or Traditional Animation).
